"Ihitha" is an Indian Hindhu female name, which in sanskrit "Iha+Hitha" combines to form Ihitha. 'Iha' means World or Earth, 'Hitha' means who does Good, Favour. In total a godess who does good for all creatures in the world.--[[User:Suneel|Suneel]] 09:20, 5 August 2006 (UTC)Suneetha & Chandrakanth Anne.